description.text:
This is a little holder for a piece of Paper.<br />
I think the clips are not working in this version. But i have no printer yet to test it.
Parameters:<br />
x = 50;<br />
y = 100;
<code >platethickness = 5;// &gt; outerborder*2

outerborder = 2;
innerborder = 1;

height = 2; //Had to be bigger than innerheight!
innerheight = 1;

isopen = 2; // 0 = not open; 1= open on X; 2= open on Y

///////////////////////RENDER OPTIONS////////////////////////
// 0 = no; 1= yes

renderPlate = 1;
renderFrame = 1;

printPosition = 0; </code>

Update 6/2/2015:  removed the old files as they are inferior to the v2 upload.  I didn't want anyone getting confused on which files to download.  I have printed about 15 of these for a project and they are working great.  This will no longer be listed as a &quot;work-in-progress&quot;  
Update 5/26/2015:  v2 uploaded.  it is now a bit larger which makes it stronger and allows for a larger screw.  Printing on my printer went from 8 minutes to 14 minutes per.  see the instructions for more information.  
Very small wire management bracket that is extremely simple and fast to print.  Created to run wires under my model railroad table.
